      • Sha256Condition

        protected Sha256Condition(CryptoConditionType type,
                          long cost,
                          byte[] fingerprint)
        Constructor that accepts a fingerprint and a cost number.
        パラメータ:
        type - A CryptoConditionType that represents the type of this condition.
        cost - A long representing the anticipated cost of this condition, calculated per the rules of the crypto-conditions specification.
        fingerprint - The binary representation of the fingerprint for this condition.

    • メソッドの詳細

      • getFingerprint

        public final byte[] getFingerprint()
        インタフェースからコピーされた説明: Condition

        A fingerprint is a binary (aka "octet") string uniquely representing the condition with respect to other conditions of the same type. Implementations which index conditions MUST use the entire string or binary encoded condition as the key - not just the fingerprint - as different conditions of different rsa may have the same fingerprint. The length and contents of the fingerprint are defined by the condition type. The fingerprint is a cryptographically secure hash of the data which defines the condition, such as a public key.

        WARNING: This method MUST perform a safe copy of the internal data to protect immutability. Callers should use Condition.getFingerprintBase64Url() instead if possible.

        戻り値:
        A read-only byte array that contains the unique fingerprint of this condition.

      • getFingerprintBase64Url

        public final String getFingerprintBase64Url()
        インタフェースからコピーされた説明: Condition

        A fingerprint is a binary (aka "octet") string uniquely representing the condition with respect to other conditions of the same type. Implementations which index conditions MUST use the entire string or binary encoded condition as the key - not just the fingerprint - as different conditions of different rsa may have the same fingerprint. The length and contents of the fingerprint are defined by the condition type. The fingerprint is a cryptographically secure hash of the data which defines the condition, such as a public key.

        戻り値:
        A Base64Url-encoded String that contains the unique fingerprint of this condition.

        protected static final byte[] hashFingerprintContents(byte[] fingerprintContents)
        Constructs the fingerprint of this condition by taking the SHA-256 digest of the contents of this condition, per the crypto-conditions RFC.
        パラメータ:
